  "id": "FG-IR-17-274",
  "title": "Use of hardcoded credentials for communication between Meru access points and FortiWLC",
  "summary": "FortiWLC included two hardcoded accounts which were used by Meru Access Points to report core dumps; these accounts had read/write privileges over various parts of the system.Starting with FortiWLC 7.0.13 and FortiWLC 8.4.0, the accounts are now completely removed and do not persist over firmware upgrade.",
